### roc functions

###############################################################
# function to create ROC and AUC data from binary classifier predictions
#
# input args: 
# pred = data.frame or data.table with first column numeric actuals (1 representing class)
#           subsequent columns representing probabilities of class from different classifiers
#           field name is name of model
#
# output args:
# rocOut[[1]] = data.table with three fields: falsePos, truePos, and modelName
#         can be fed straight into ggplot for plotting
#         ggplot(rocOut[1], aes(x = falsePos, y = truePos, group = modelName, colour = modelName)) + geom_line()
#
# rocOut[[2]] = data.table with two fields: modelName and auc
#
# rocOut[[3]] = data.table with three fields: threshold, accuracy, and modelName
#         can be fed straight into ggplot for plotting
#         ggplot(rocOut[3], aes(x = thresh, y = acc, group = modelName, colour = modelName)) + geom_line()
#
# sample data 
# tmppred = predictions[, -1, with=FALSE]
# pred = predictions
# tmprocout = genROC(tmppred)
# rm(tmprocOut)
# rm(tmpaucOut)
#
#
## ps Sept 2014
########################################

genROC = function(pred) {
  
  require(ROCR)
  require(data.table)
  
  # create roc data and manipulate for plotting (ROC and AUC)
  rocrPredOut = prediction(pred, pred[, c(rep(1, ncol(pred))), with=FALSE])
  rocrPerfOut = performance(rocrPredOut, "tpr", "fpr")
  rocrAUCOut = performance(rocrPredOut, "auc")
  
  rocOut1 = data.table(falsePos=rocrPerfOut@x.values[[1]], truePos=rocrPerfOut@y.values[[1]], modelName = "actual")
  rocOut2 = data.table(auc=rocrAUCOut@y.values[[1]], modelName = "actual")
  
  for (i in 2:length(rocrPerfOut@alpha.values)) {
    #i=1
    rocOut1 = rbindlist(list(rocOut1, data.table(falsePos=rocrPerfOut@x.values[[i]], truePos=rocrPerfOut@y.values[[i]], modelName = colnames(pred)[i]))) 
    rocOut2 = rbindlist(list(rocOut2, data.table(auc=rocrAUCOut@y.values[[i]], modelName = colnames(pred)[i]))) 
  }
  
  # create accuracy at different thresholds
  threshD = 0.1
  tmp = colSums((pred>0)==(pred[, c(rep(1, ncol(pred))), with=FALSE]>0)) / nrow(pred)
  rocOut3 = data.table(threshold = 0, modelName = names(tmp), accuracy = tmp)
  for (thresh in seq(threshD,1-threshD,threshD)) {
    #thresh = 0.1
    tmp = colSums((pred>thresh)==(pred[, c(rep(1, ncol(pred))), with=FALSE]>thresh)) / nrow(pred)
    rocOut3 = rbindlist(list(rocOut3, data.table(threshold = thresh, modelName = names(tmp), accuracy = tmp)))
  }
  
  setkeyv(rocOut1, c("modelName", "falsePos"))
  setkeyv(rocOut2, "modelName")
  setkeyv(rocOut3, c("modelName", "threshold"))
  
  return(list(rocOut1,rocOut2,rocOut3))
}
